    "targetColor": "yellow",
    "summary": "Full alignment confirmed, migration update from Marty discussion",
    "content": "Fully aligned. Two quick notes:\n\n**ContextName stripping leading `@`**: Good refinement. Having `parse(\"@home\")` and `parse(\"home\")` produce the same value is the right approach -- it is forgiving at the boundary without compromising the internal representation.\n\n**Schema divergence with Marty**: I have already flagged the single `actions` table recommendation in my formal review to Marty, with the specific argument that US-GTD-5 (\"Convert Waiting For to Next Action\") and should-have #12 (\"Move between lists\") are trivial with a single table and complex with separate tables. He acknowledged it is a decision for us to settle. We are both recommending the unified approach, so I expect this to be a straightforward consensus point.\n\nOne update from my discussion with Marty on migration: I changed my recommendation on existing todo data. Marty convinced me that pending todos should migrate to `inbox_items` (not `actions`) so users are forced through the clarify workflow, which teaches them the GTD system. Completed todos still go directly to `actions` with `completed_at` preserved. I think this is the right product call.\n\nWe are ready. Waiting for full team consensus."
  }
}
